    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A thematic, non-linear dashboard structure. The user starts with a high-level summary (The Thesis) and can navigate via a persistent header to deep-dive sections: Technology, Market Landscape, The Core Opportunity, and Strategic Scenarios. This structure prioritizes user-led exploration over a rigid, linear report format, allowing a busy executive to jump directly to areas of interest. Key interactions involve toggling data on charts and switching between comparative views to make complex data easily digestible. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Thesis KPIs: Goal=Inform. Method=Large stat cards. Interaction=None. Justification=Immediate high-impact data.
        - D3O Tech Comparison: Goal=Compare. Method=Bar Chart (Chart.js). Interaction=Buttons to switch between D3O variants. Justification=Clearly visualizes the performance trade-offs between protection and flexibility.
        - Competitive Matrix: Goal=Analyze. Method=Radar Chart (Chart.js). Interaction=Buttons to select competitor. Justification=Provides a powerful multi-axis visual comparison of D3O's advantages.
        - Iron Triangle: Goal=Organize/Persuade. Method=HTML/CSS Diagram. Interaction=Click to "break" the triangle. Justification=Memorable visualization of the core market failure and D3O's unique solution.
        - GTM Strategies: Goal=Compare. Method=Tabbed Interface. Interaction=Clicking tabs. Justification=Standard, clean UI for presenting distinct options.
        - Roadmap: Goal=Inform. Method=HTML/CSS Timeline. Interaction=Hover effects. Justification=Intuitive for chronological data.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
